The paper deals with the performance of multiantenna receivers in wireless networks, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of information theory (cs.IT), networking and internet architecture (cs.NI), signal processing (cs.SI), multiagent systems (cs.MA), and performance analysis (cs.PF). The paper specifically focuses on the characterization of the signal-to-interference-plus-noise ratio (SINR) in a wireless network with transmitting nodes distributed according to a doubly stochastic process, which is a generalization of the Poisson point process. This suggests that the paper is likely to be relevant to researchers working in the above-mentioned sub-categories.
